  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "ONSET coupling. Drum hits create phase disruption — each percussion event scatters the Kuramoto field like a shockwave through the partial bank. The voice is held at moderate sync; ONSET's transients periodically shatter it, and the partials scramble to re-synchronize. The time between hits IS the drama — the longer the gap, the more the choir recovers before the next impact.",
